p: Overall, 43 constituents were identified in the six fractions of R. graveolens fruit EO ( Suppl. Table S1). Ketones (including alkyl ketone) were the most abundant class in the control oil (69.2%) in the 10–30, 30–60, and 60–90 min fractions out of the total EO ( Table 2). The major constituents of ketones were 2-nonanone and 2-undecanone ( Table 3).
